TERMINAL ACTION RECONCILIATION MODE

The primary RequestPolicy is credential-bearing but omitted a non-method-mandated terminal_action. Return only JSON in
this exact shape:
{"version":"1","criterion_id":"c0","terminal_action_family":"request"}

- criterion_id must select exactly one existing criterion ID from PRIMARY COMPLETION CRITERIA, or be null to abstain.
- terminal_action_family must be request|application|form|order when criterion_id is non-null, or null when abstaining.
- Select a criterion only when the latest request requires authentication followed by creating or submitting that
  criterion's request, application, or form outcome, or placing an order.
- Abstain when the requested end state is successful authentication itself, including MFA, or when no single existing
  criterion unambiguously represents the post-login terminal action.
- Preserve criterion identity: do not invent, remove, duplicate, paraphrase, or re-order criteria. Do not select a
  method-mandated criterion. The server changes only the selected criterion's kind and terminal_action_family.

